1
00:01:11,360 --> 00:01:13,039
Knowing Matsuda,

2
00:01:13,520 --> 00:01:15,320
he must have suspected this place.

3
00:01:15,320 --> 00:01:16,240
This transmission spot

4
00:01:16,240 --> 00:01:17,840
can no longer be used for now.

5
00:01:18,480 --> 00:01:19,740
What should we do then?

6
00:01:22,080 --> 00:01:23,010
Here's the plan.

7
00:01:23,240 --> 00:01:24,570
I'll take the radio back

8
00:01:24,680 --> 00:01:26,840
to be the backup radio for Shunfa Advertising.

9
00:01:26,840 --> 00:01:29,370
I will send tonight's unfinished telegraphs

10
00:01:29,760 --> 00:01:30,640
tomorrow.

11
00:01:34,320 --> 00:01:34,920
Okay.

12
00:01:35,560 --> 00:01:36,360
Be safe.

13
00:01:53,440 --> 00:01:54,200
What is it?

14
00:02:06,840 --> 00:02:08,560
Mr. Shen, what are you doing?

15
00:02:09,240 --> 00:02:10,840
I discussed a deal with the Japanese

16
00:02:10,840 --> 00:02:12,360
and came back a little late.

17
00:02:12,360 --> 00:02:14,320
Take this and share it with your brothers.

18
00:02:14,320 --> 00:02:16,050
Thanks for the treat, Mr. Shen.

19
00:02:20,040 --> 00:02:21,100
What are you doing?

20
00:02:21,720 --> 00:02:22,400
Sir.

21
00:02:22,800 --> 00:02:23,640
Mr. Shen.

22
00:02:23,920 --> 00:02:26,650
A big boss doing business with the Imperial Army.

23
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:28,850
Here, sir, have a taste.

24
00:02:29,360 --> 00:02:30,420
It's from Mr. Shen.

25
00:02:33,440 --> 00:02:34,280
Good evening.

26
00:02:36,480 --> 00:02:37,200
Brothers,

27
00:02:37,400 --> 00:02:39,280
let Mr. Shen's car pass.

28
00:02:40,920 --> 00:02:42,440
Take care, Mr. Shen.

29
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:45,000
Sister Qin.

30
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:48,000
Kong Xuzhou from the Harmonica Society is a patriotic youth.

31
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:49,120
He works at the Harbin Broadcasting Bureau

32
00:02:49,120 --> 00:02:50,640
as a broadcaster and editor.

33
00:02:50,640 --> 00:02:51,960
I want to quickly rehearse

34
00:02:51,960 --> 00:02:53,200
'The Song of the Great Road' and 'The Pioneer' with everyone

35
00:02:53,200 --> 00:02:54,720
to perform at the Broadcasting Bureau.

36
00:02:54,720 --> 00:02:56,040
Let Xiao Kong broadcast

37
00:02:56,040 --> 00:02:57,770
these songs through the radio.

38
00:02:58,560 --> 00:02:59,320
Xiaoxiong.

39
00:03:00,400 --> 00:03:02,400
The Secret Service just checked us.

40
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:05,240
The Harmonica Society is at the center of attention right now.

41
00:03:05,240 --> 00:03:06,100
How about this?

42
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:07,370
You lead the members

43
00:03:07,440 --> 00:03:09,320
to rehearse these songs first.

44
00:03:09,840 --> 00:03:12,500
As for letting Xiao Kong broadcast on the radio,

45
00:03:13,040 --> 00:03:14,120
we will wait for a chance.

46
00:03:14,120 --> 00:03:14,880
Sister Qin.

47
00:03:15,440 --> 00:03:18,079
I joined the Harmonica Society to use music as a weapon,

48
00:03:18,079 --> 00:03:19,680
treating the harmonica as a second gun,

49
00:03:19,680 --> 00:03:20,520
to promote resisting Japan and saving the country,

50
00:03:20,520 --> 00:03:23,720
and to prevent those young people from being subjugated.

51
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:26,520
You are a member of the Communist Youth League.

52
00:03:26,520 --> 00:03:28,200
I know you and I understand you.

53
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:29,120
But Xiaoxiong,

54
00:03:29,880 --> 00:03:33,040
resisting Japan and saving the country requires more than just passion.

55
00:03:33,040 --> 00:03:35,170
It requires resilience and patience,

56
00:03:35,480 --> 00:03:37,340
and the wisdom to fight the enemy.

57
00:03:37,760 --> 00:03:38,640
Sometimes,

58
00:03:39,480 --> 00:03:42,740
you still need to do superficial work to confuse the enemy.

59
00:03:45,480 --> 00:03:46,440
Okay.

60
00:04:31,960 --> 00:04:33,320
What? The radio is gone?

61
00:04:34,320 --> 00:04:35,200
Just in case,

62
00:04:35,440 --> 00:04:37,720
Heming, don't go back to the advertising agency

63
00:04:37,720 --> 00:04:39,180
or the Harmonica Society.

64
00:04:39,520 --> 00:04:40,520
If the radio

65
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:42,920
was really taken by the Japanese or secret agents,

66
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:44,680
you must leave Harbin immediately.

67
00:04:44,680 --> 00:04:45,360
No.

68
00:04:45,920 --> 00:04:46,760
The unfinished telegraphs from last night

69
00:04:46,760 --> 00:04:47,820
must be sent today.

70
00:04:48,720 --> 00:04:50,200
Those are the coordinates of the Japanese army's warehouse.

71
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:51,720
If the guerrillas know it and carry out an explosion,

72
00:04:51,720 --> 00:04:55,520
they can destroy a large amount of the enemy's logistics materials.

73
00:05:03,400 --> 00:05:04,530
It's the fifth case.

74
00:05:05,280 --> 00:05:07,320
Still that damn killing message.

75
00:05:12,280 --> 00:05:12,920
Section Chief Qian.

76
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:14,040
Captain, I'm here.

77
00:05:15,040 --> 00:05:16,600
Acting alone or in a gang?

78
00:05:17,120 --> 00:05:18,200
We've been investigating for so long,

79
00:05:18,200 --> 00:05:20,060
how come there are no clues at all?

80
00:05:20,160 --> 00:05:21,200
We wouldn't dare slack off.

81
00:05:21,200 --> 00:05:22,720
We've been investigating non-stop.

82
00:05:22,720 --> 00:05:24,520
But this killer is too slippery.

83
00:05:24,840 --> 00:05:26,600
The time of the crimes is extremely irregular.

84
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:28,600
It could be three months or half a year.

85
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:30,000
But in my opinion,

86
00:05:30,240 --> 00:05:32,370
there definitely aren't many of them.

87
00:05:35,760 --> 00:05:36,440
Chief.

88
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:39,640
Could it be the work of the Anti-Japanese Traitor Eradication Corps?

89
00:05:39,640 --> 00:05:40,640
That's absolutely impossible.

90
00:05:40,640 --> 00:05:43,370
The Eradication Corps always leaves their name.

91
00:05:43,400 --> 00:05:44,640
This coward

92
00:05:45,040 --> 00:05:46,680
only dares to leave a message.

93
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:48,480
He hides his name.

94
00:05:55,040 --> 00:05:55,840
Chief Qian.

95
00:05:56,800 --> 00:05:58,860
If you don't catch him within a month,

96
00:05:59,640 --> 00:06:00,840
you're on your own.

97
00:06:02,920 --> 00:06:03,560
Yes, sir.

98
00:06:10,360 --> 00:06:10,920
Sister Qin.

99
00:06:10,920 --> 00:06:11,600
Lingzi.

100
00:06:12,440 --> 00:06:15,040
I just came back from Comrade Zhang Dajiang's.

101
00:06:15,480 --> 00:06:16,880
He asked me to inform you.

102
00:06:16,920 --> 00:06:18,040
To prevent being located

103
00:06:18,040 --> 00:06:19,640
by the enemy's radio detection vehicles,

104
00:06:19,640 --> 00:06:22,440
each transmission must not exceed three minutes.

105
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:24,360
This is the time limit for the enemy's

106
00:06:24,360 --> 00:06:26,760
radio detection vehicles to pinpoint the exact location.

107
00:06:26,760 --> 00:06:27,490
Don't worry.

108
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:29,530
Have some water and take your time.

109
00:06:32,520 --> 00:06:34,400
Also, when sending important intelligence,

110
00:06:34,400 --> 00:06:36,120
use mobile transmission tactics.

111
00:06:36,120 --> 00:06:36,760
In one night,

112
00:06:36,760 --> 00:06:39,080
the same telegram must be sent at least twice

113
00:06:39,080 --> 00:06:40,800
in different locations.

114
00:06:42,400 --> 00:06:43,130
Understood.

115
00:06:43,680 --> 00:06:44,400
What else?

116
00:06:45,280 --> 00:06:46,520
During mobile transmission,

117
00:06:46,520 --> 00:06:49,520
the radio and the operator must take separate routes.

118
00:06:50,080 --> 00:06:52,610
To avoid being caught all at once by the enemy.

119
00:07:04,160 --> 00:07:05,600
Chen Lao'er, are you crazy?

120
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:06,520
You scared me.

121
00:07:07,400 --> 00:07:10,400
Wandering around during the school summer vacation.

122
00:07:10,960 --> 00:07:12,890
Why didn't you come straight home?

123
00:07:12,960 --> 00:07:14,960
Why did you go to the harmonica club?

124
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:16,200
Deputy Chief Chen.

125
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:18,480
I heard you

126
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:21,000
turned the harmonica club upside down last night.

127
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:22,260
Did you find anything?

128
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:25,400
If we didn't turn the harmonica club upside down,

129
00:07:25,400 --> 00:07:27,060
I wouldn't be looking for you.

130
00:07:27,480 --> 00:07:28,410
What do you mean?

131
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:30,460
Answer my question first.

132
00:07:31,160 --> 00:07:33,480
I went to learn the harmonica.

133
00:07:34,320 --> 00:07:36,180
Why do you care about everything?

134
00:07:39,440 --> 00:07:42,960
The harmonica club only holds classes on Sunday during the day.

135
00:07:42,960 --> 00:07:44,560
All other times are at night.

136
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:49,080
I had something to see Sister Qin about. So what?

137
00:07:49,080 --> 00:07:49,800
What is it?

138
00:07:51,560 --> 00:07:52,320
Chen Lao'er.

139
00:07:52,640 --> 00:07:55,240
If you keep asking questions, I'll ignore you.

140
00:07:58,520 --> 00:07:59,120
Come here.

141
00:07:59,400 --> 00:08:00,080
What?

142
00:08:04,280 --> 00:08:05,140
Let me tell you,

143
00:08:05,320 --> 00:08:07,450
the harmonica club isn't a good place.

144
00:08:07,480 --> 00:08:09,120
You're not allowed to go there anymore.

145
00:08:09,120 --> 00:08:10,650
Chen Lao'er, make it clear.

146
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:12,200
Why isn't the harmonica club a good place?

147
00:08:12,200 --> 00:08:13,330
Glaring at me again.

148
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:18,040
Does Qin Na really think

149
00:08:18,240 --> 00:08:20,700
I didn't see the problem with that wardrobe?

150
00:08:21,920 --> 00:08:22,840
Last night,

151
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:24,920
the transmission took too long,

152
00:08:24,920 --> 00:08:27,780
which led to the Special Service Section's search.

153
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:29,260
Special Service Section.

154
00:08:29,600 --> 00:08:30,530
Chen Yu came too.

155
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:31,560
I just don't know

156
00:08:32,280 --> 00:08:34,010
when he searched the wardrobe.

157
00:08:34,240 --> 00:08:36,370
Did you really not notice the problem,

158
00:08:36,760 --> 00:08:38,360
or are you pretending not to?

159
00:08:39,320 --> 00:08:41,360
Chen Yu, listen to me carefully.

160
00:08:41,720 --> 00:08:43,049
Qin Na is my good friend.

161
00:08:55,960 --> 00:08:57,040
What you just said

162
00:08:57,240 --> 00:08:58,440
must be kept a secret.

163
00:08:58,920 --> 00:09:00,840
If it weren't for your good relationship with Qin Na,

164
00:09:00,840 --> 00:09:02,640
I wouldn't take the blame for this.

165
00:09:02,640 --> 00:09:04,040
This could get us killed.

166
00:09:04,680 --> 00:09:06,080
Now that's a true friend.

167
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:07,040
Then

168
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:09,400
give me a kiss.

169
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:11,360
In your dreams.

170
00:09:11,400 --> 00:09:12,200
I'm leaving.

171
00:09:13,160 --> 00:09:13,760
Lingzi,

172
00:09:14,080 --> 00:09:16,160
you must remember what I just told you.

173
00:09:16,160 --> 00:09:18,290
You must also remember what I told you.

174
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:24,640
I want to play a song for everyone,

175
00:09:24,640 --> 00:09:26,370
'Song of the Great Manchuria'.

176
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:28,640
Now I will play it for you.

177
00:09:31,560 --> 00:09:32,490
What did you say?

178
00:09:34,280 --> 00:09:36,280
I'm asking you. What did you say?

179
00:09:41,800 --> 00:09:42,600
Let me go!

180
00:09:43,120 --> 00:09:45,520
I said, since you praise it so much,

181
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:47,760
why don't you go play it for the Japanese?

182
00:09:47,760 --> 00:09:48,820
Listen, everyone!

183
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:51,520
She said 'Song of the Great Manchuria' sounds terrible.

184
00:09:51,520 --> 00:09:53,400
She is an anti-Japanese activist!

185
00:09:53,400 --> 00:09:54,320
I'm going to report her.

186
00:09:54,320 --> 00:09:54,760
Come with me.

187
00:09:54,760 --> 00:09:55,920
What are you doing? Let go!

188
00:09:55,920 --> 00:09:58,400
Go! Picking on a girl, what kind of man are you?

189
00:09:58,400 --> 00:09:59,160
You hit me?

190
00:09:59,240 --> 00:10:00,040
So what if I hit you?

191
00:10:00,040 --> 00:10:00,900
Let me tell you,

192
00:10:00,960 --> 00:10:02,720
our great Northeast has its own music.

193
00:10:02,720 --> 00:10:04,200
'Moon over the Battlefield' sounds much better than this.

194
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:05,680
You are also a reactionary!

195
00:10:05,680 --> 00:10:06,800
I'm going to report you.

196
00:10:06,800 --> 00:10:07,600
Are you coming with me?

197
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:09,280
Fine, let's go. Who's afraid of you?

198
00:10:09,280 --> 00:10:10,940
Let's go. Who's afraid of you?

199
00:10:11,280 --> 00:10:12,340
What are you doing?

200
00:10:12,440 --> 00:10:13,160
What?

201
00:10:13,520 --> 00:10:14,960
Stop! What are you doing?

202
00:10:15,240 --> 00:10:15,960
Sir,

203
00:10:16,280 --> 00:10:18,160
he said 'Song of the Great Manchuria' sounds terrible.

204
00:10:18,160 --> 00:10:18,880
I didn't.

205
00:10:19,040 --> 00:10:20,720
I just said 'Moon over the Battlefield' sounds better,

206
00:10:20,720 --> 00:10:22,280
and it's harder to play.

207
00:10:23,080 --> 00:10:23,640
You did!

208
00:10:23,760 --> 00:10:26,000
- I didn't!
- You did!

209
00:10:26,080 --> 00:10:27,120
Alright, stop.

210
00:10:27,240 --> 00:10:28,520
Stop!

211
00:10:28,720 --> 00:10:29,450
Listen to me.

212
00:10:30,120 --> 00:10:30,880
Students,

213
00:10:31,480 --> 00:10:32,810
music knows no borders,

214
00:10:33,160 --> 00:10:34,560
but we have our homeland.

215
00:10:35,080 --> 00:10:37,010
Our homeland is our true paradise.

216
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:39,920
You can play 'Song of the Great Manchuria',

217
00:10:39,920 --> 00:10:41,560
and you can play 'Moon over the Battlefield'.

218
00:10:41,560 --> 00:10:43,880
But we are here to study and share music.

219
00:10:44,320 --> 00:10:45,760
Let's not report and accuse each other.

220
00:10:45,760 --> 00:10:46,400
Okay?

221
00:10:47,200 --> 00:10:47,880
Students,

222
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:49,130
Captain Gu is right.

223
00:10:49,160 --> 00:10:51,200
It's normal to have differences in music.

224
00:10:51,200 --> 00:10:51,840
But

225
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:53,800
we shouldn't report each other.

226
00:10:54,040 --> 00:10:54,970
If in the future,

227
00:10:55,160 --> 00:10:57,160
you have any questions about music,

228
00:10:57,360 --> 00:10:59,620
you are welcome to come and discuss them.

229
00:10:59,760 --> 00:11:02,290
I hope you all achieve academic success here.

230
00:11:02,440 --> 00:11:03,120
Okay?

231
00:11:03,400 --> 00:11:04,080
Okay.

232
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:05,800
Alright.

233
00:11:06,080 --> 00:11:08,140
Pack your things. Class is starting.

234
00:11:09,840 --> 00:11:11,440
I have notified the Power Supply Bureau.

235
00:11:11,440 --> 00:11:12,200
Tonight,

236
00:11:12,400 --> 00:11:13,560
they are ready to cooperate with us

237
00:11:13,560 --> 00:11:15,490
to cut off power to Butou District.

238
00:11:15,680 --> 00:11:16,440
Suzuki,

239
00:11:17,640 --> 00:11:20,760
how accurate is the detection with power outage by zones?

240
00:11:20,760 --> 00:11:21,440
Captain,

241
00:11:21,960 --> 00:11:24,520
I should say the accuracy is extremely high.

242
00:11:25,880 --> 00:11:27,320
In the areas surrounding Butou District,

243
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:29,650
no suspicious radio waves have appeared.

244
00:11:30,600 --> 00:11:32,440
The radio station from last night

245
00:11:32,440 --> 00:11:34,170
must be within Butou District.

246
00:11:36,320 --> 00:11:37,360
Once a signal is detected,

247
00:11:37,360 --> 00:11:38,360
cut off the power immediately.

248
00:11:38,360 --> 00:11:39,040
Yes.

249
00:12:28,480 --> 00:12:29,240
Is it assembled?

250
00:12:29,240 --> 00:12:29,920
Yeah.

251
00:12:30,640 --> 00:12:31,370
Let's start.

252
00:12:43,680 --> 00:12:46,410
You must finish sending it within three minutes.

253
00:13:15,960 --> 00:13:16,800
Mr. Suzuki,

254
00:13:17,760 --> 00:13:22,620
suspicious radio waves have appeared in the area of Xinshi Street and Youzheng Street.

255
00:13:28,280 --> 00:13:29,600
It's the same frequency band.

256
00:13:29,600 --> 00:13:30,960
The underground party has moved that radio station

257
00:13:30,960 --> 00:13:33,690
to the area of Xinshi Street and Youzheng Street.

258
00:13:34,880 --> 00:13:37,080
Get to Youzheng Street in two minutes!

259
00:14:24,240 --> 00:14:24,880
Hurry up!
